kdl.prox.qgraph2
Class AbstractQuery

java.lang.Object
  kdl.prox.qgraph2.AbstractQuery
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
Query, Subquery
public abstract class AbstractQuery
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

Abstract superclass to Query and Subquery. Represents a (possibly augmented) query. Contains QGEdge and QGVertex instances that represent a QGraph 2.0 query. We say "augmented" because it can contain QGCompVertex instances (consolidated nodes). Global QGItem name uniqueness is guaranteed if the addXX() methods are used. Works with the AbsQueryChild interface: All classes that can be contained by me (QGItem - QGVertex and QGEdge - and Subquery) must implement AbsQueryChild.

qgItemForName

public QGItem qgItemForName(java.lang.String qgItemName)
Returns the first item in me that has exactly one name in its names, where that name equals (honoring case) qgItemName. Checks in this order: vertices, edges, then my subqueries (recurses). Returns null if no items have that name. This overload takes a String.

setConstEle

public void setConstEle(org.jdom.Element constEle)
Sets my constEle to constEle. NB: In order to make serialization-based copying more efficient, constEle.detach() should be called by the caller. It is not done here because it causes ConcurrentModificationException while iterating in QueryGraph2CompOp.queryFromQueryBodyEles().
